      <h3>Anna Joseph, LCSW, MPH</h3>
      <p>I have been a Licensed Clinical Social Worker (LCSW) in Colorado since 2019. I hold a dual Master of Social Work (MSW) and Master of Public Health (MPH) degree from the University of Michigan.</p>
      <p>As a therapist, my goal is to support people in leading lives that feel meaningful, where they can show up as their authentic selves and align their actions with the person they want to be. My approach to therapy is rooted in Acceptance and Commitment Therapy (ACT), and I also incorporate Dialectical Behavioral Therapy (DBT) and Motivational Interviewing to tailor treatment to each individual’s needs.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

